flowchart TB
    %% This diagram mirrors OpenZeppelin RWA vocabulary:
    %% - Token core calls into a separate Shibui Identity Layer module
    %% - Compliance is modular and remains independent from identity proof format

    subgraph TokenLayer["ERC-3643 Token Layer (Token Core + Compliance)"]
        Token["Token Contract (ERC-3643)"]
        Compliance["Compliance Module(s)"]
        IR["Identity Registry"]
    end

    subgraph IdentityVerifierLayer["Shibui Identity Layer (pluggable)"]
        ECV["Shibui Verifier (EAS)\nEASClaimVerifier"]
        TIA["Trusted Attesters Adapter\nEASTrustedIssuersAdapter"]
        EIP["Wallet→Identity Mapping\nEASIdentityProxy"]
        CTR["Claim Topics Registry\n(ERC-3643)"]
    end

    subgraph EASLayer["EAS Protocol Layer"]
        EAS["EAS.sol"]
        SR["Schema Registry"]
    end

    subgraph OnchainIDLayer["ONCHAINID Verifier Module (optional)"]
        OCID["ONCHAINID Contract"]
        TIR["TrustedIssuersRegistry"]
        IRS["IdentityRegistryStorage"]
    end

    Token -->|canTransfer| Compliance
    Compliance -->|isVerified| IR

    %% ERC-3643 Identity Registry delegates identity checks to the Shibui verifier module.
    IR -->|EAS Identity Verifier| ECV

    %% Optional dual-mode: keep ONCHAINID as an alternative verifier.
    IR -.->|ONCHAINID Verifier| IRS
    IRS -.-> OCID
    OCID -.-> TIR

    %% Internals of the EAS Identity Verifier module
    ECV -->|resolve identity| EIP
    ECV -->|required topics| CTR
    ECV -->|trusted attesters| TIA
    ECV -->|read attestations| EAS

    EAS --> SR

